        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 5:39AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 538 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Griggs, or 18 miles north of Stratford, moving
southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Goodwell and Texhoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
